{"post_stream":{"posts":[{"id":3172386,"name":"97ing","username":"97ing","avatar_template":"/letter_avatar_proxy/v4/letter/9/5fc32e/{size}.png","created_at":"2023-03-24T21:24:15.629Z","cooked":"<p>Hello!<br>
I’m trying to use NetworkTables to connect with the robot for vision.<br>
I’m following the “<a href="https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/networktables/client-side-program.html" rel="noopener nofollow ugc">Creating a Client-side Program</a>” documentation.</p>
<p>I’m running Python on the Pi. The Pi has the 2022.1.1 Romi image on it, as newer versions did not work on the pi 3.</p>
<p>Unfortunately, it appears that <code>ntcore</code> is not installed properly, as it kept on complaining about it. I instead did <code>pip install ntcore</code>, but now it gives me the following:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">AttributeError: module 'ntcore' has no attribute 'NetworkTableInstance'
</code></pre>
<p>I had tried installing the <code>pyntcore</code> library with <code>sudo pip3 install -U pyntcore</code>, but I always get the following error:</p>
<pre><code class="lang-auto">
Command "/usr/bin/python3 -m pip install --ignore-installed --no-user --prefix /tmp/pip-build-env-ggq4i9rr --no-warn-script-location --no-binary :none: --only-binary :none: -i https://pypi.org/simple --extra-index-url https://www.piwheels.org/simple -- robotpy-build&lt;2024.0.0,&gt;=2023.1.1 robotpy-wpiutil~=2023.4.2 robotpy-wpinet~=2023.4.2" failed with error code 1 in None
</code></pre>
<p>Does anyone know what is going on here? I would really appreciate the help!</p>
<p>The full code for the robot (publisher side, Java):</p>
<pre><code class="lang-java">public class EasyNetworkTableExample extends TimedRobot {
  DoublePublisher xPub;
  DoublePublisher yPub;

  public void robotInit() {
    // Get the default instance of NetworkTables that was created automatically
    // when the robot program starts
    NetworkTableInstance inst = NetworkTableInstance.getDefault();

    // Get the table within that instance that contains the data. There can
    // be as many tables as you like and exist to make it easier to organize
    // your data. In this case, it's a table called datatable.
    NetworkTable table = inst.getTable("datatable");

    // Start publishing topics within that table that correspond to the X and Y
    // values
    // for some operation in your program.
    // The topic names are actually "/datatable/x" and "/datatable/y".
    xPub = table.getDoubleTopic("x").publish();
    yPub = table.getDoubleTopic("y").publish();
  }

  double x = 0;
  double y = 0;

  public void teleopPeriodic() {
    // Publish values that are constantly increasing.
    xPub.set(x);
    yPub.set(y);
    x += 0.05;
    y += 1.0;
  }
}
</code></pre>
<p>The full code subscriber side (raspberry pi, Python):</p>
<pre><code class="lang-python">import ntcore
import time

if __name__ == "__main__":
    inst = ntcore.NetworkTableInstance.getDefault()
    table = inst.getTable("datatable")
    xSub = table.getDoubleTopic("x").subscribe(0)
    ySub = table.getDoubleTopic("y").subscribe(0)
    inst.startClient4("example client")
    inst.setServerTeam(8574) # where TEAM=190, 294, etc, or use inst.setServer("hostname") or similar
    inst.startDSClient() # recommended if running on DS computer; this gets the robot IP from the DS

    while True:
        time.sleep(1)

        x = xSub.get()
        y = ySub.get()
        print(f"X: {x} Y: {y}")
</code></pre>","post_number":1,"post_type":1,"posts_count":3,"updated_at":"2023-03-24T21:24:15.629Z","reply_count":1,"reply_to_post_number":null,"quote_count":0,"incoming_link_count":271,"reads":77,"readers_count":76,"score":1390.4,"yours":false,"topic_id":431625,"topic_slug":"ntcore-is-not-a-module-raspberry-pi-vision","display_username":"97ing","primary_group_name":null,"flair_name":null,"flair_url":null,"flair_bg_color":null,"flair_color":null,"flair_group_id":null,"badges_granted":[],"version":1,"can_edit":false,"can_delete":false,"can_recover":false,"can_see_hidden_post":true,"can_wiki":false,"link_counts":[{"url":"https://docs.wpilib.org/en/stable/docs/software/networktables/client-side-program.html","internal":false,"reflection":false,"title":"Creating a Client-side Program — FIRST Robotics Competition documentation","clicks":8}],"read":true,"user_title":"","bookmarked":false,"actions_summary":[{"id":2,"count":1}],"moderator":false,"admin":false,"staff":false,"user_id":58031,"hidden":false,"trust_level":1,"deleted_at":null,"user_deleted":false,"edit_reason":null,"can_view_edit_history":true,"wiki":false,"post_url":"/t/ntcore-is-not-a-module-raspberry-pi-vision/431625/1","custom_user_title":null,"reactions":[{"id":"heart","type":"emoji","count":1}],"current_user_reaction":null,"reaction_users_count":1,"current_user_used_main_reaction":false,"can_accept_answer":false,"can_unaccept_answer":false,"accepted_answer":false,"topic_accepted_answer":null,"can_vote":false},{"id":3172434,"name":"Joe Ross","username":"Joe_Ross","avatar_template":"/user_avatar/www.chiefdelphi.com/joe_ross/{size}/37_2.png","created_at":"2023-03-24T23:03:57.778Z","cooked":"<aside class="quote no-group" data-username="97ing" data-post="1" data-topic="431625">
